8.42	Atrani	Atrani	Atrani is a town and comune on the Amalfi Coast in the province of Salerno in the Campania region of south-western Italy. It is located on the outskirts of Amalfi, several minutes drive down the coast. On the night of 9 September 2010, Atrani was the scene of severe flooding and mudslides caused by the Dragone River bursting its banks.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f7/Atrani.JPG/250px-Atrani.JPG
